misc: Passed the Federal civil service examination around 1890.  While a stenographer in the Navy Dept., took a prize for writing 37,000 words in shorthand on a postcard.  Studied pharmacy in the evenings and won the scholarship prize of the "Pharmaceutical Era" in a class of 1,015; this scholarship assured him coverage of all college expenses at whichever pharmaceutical school in the US or Canada he might select.
After 1884, attended special courses in orificial surgery in Baltimore, MD, and in psychotherapeutics in Chicago, IL.
